---
export const prerender = true;
---
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
<title>About Orient — infrastructure for alignment</title>
<meta name="description" content="Orient builds the systems that keep communication coherent as it moves — so meaning survives every handoff and understanding compounds instead of decaying." />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Spectral:ital,wght@0,300;0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400;1,500&family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/orient.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/landing.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/about.css?v=3" />

{import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID && (
  <>
    <script async src={`https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=${import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID}`}></script>
    <script is:inline define:vars={{ gaId: import.meta.env.PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID }}>
      window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
      function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);}
      gtag('js', new Date());
      gtag('config', gaId);
    </script>
  </>
)}

</head>
<body class="ab-page">

<!-- ============ HEADER ============ -->
<header class="site-header" id="header">
  <div class="wrap bar">
    <a href="/" class="brand" aria-label="Orient — home">
      <img src="/logo.svg" alt="Orient" class="brand-logo" />
    </a>
    <nav class="site-nav">
      <a href="/">What is Orient</a>
      <a href="/forhumans">For Humans</a>
      <a href="/formachines">For Machines</a>
      <a href="/usecases">Use cases</a>
      <a href="#top" aria-current="page" style="color:var(--ink)">About</a>
    </nav>
    <button class="btn" data-scroll="#access">Request access</button>
  </div>
</header>

<main id="top">

  <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
  <section class="ab-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">About Orient</span>
      <h1>We build the systems that keep communication coherent as it <em>moves</em>.</h1>
      <p class="lede">Orient helps meaning survive every handoff — so teams move with <b>clarity</b>, <b>speed</b>, and shared purpose, and understanding compounds instead of decaying.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ PROBLEM ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-problem">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="lead">Organisations produce more communication than ever — decks, briefs, documents, updates and AI-generated material — and <span class="hl">assume alignment follows.</span> <span class="mut">It rarely does.</span></p>
      <p class="sub">As ideas move across teams, meetings and tools, meaning shifts, intent fragments, and decisions drift. The output keeps accelerating; the shared understanding does not.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ THESIS ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-thesis">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p>In the AI era, the edge isn't faster output. It's <span class="em">durable alignment</span>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ STORY BLOCKS ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-story">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="ab-block">
        <div class="lbl">Why we built Orient</div>
        <div>
          <h2>Clarity at creation, confusion in motion.</h2>
          <p>We built Orient after watching the same failure repeat across organisations: a message is sharp the moment it's made, then loses meaning with every retelling. Teams could produce more communication than ever, but had no system for preserving what it meant as it moved.</p>
          <p>Our background spans reasoning systems, language models, agentic architectures, optimisation and vision — the cutting edge of applied AI. Across every domain the pattern was identical: <b>output accelerated, but shared understanding did not.</b> Orient is our answer to that gap.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ab-block">
        <div class="lbl">Who this is for</div>
        <div>
          <h2>Organisations operating in complexity.</h2>
          <p>Orient is for companies where strategy, decisions, research and communication move across many teams, formats and stakeholders — where the cost of misunderstanding is real.</p>
          <ul class="ab-for">
            <li>Leadership and strategy teams</li>
            <li>Product, research and cross-functional organisations</li>
            <li>Companies where communication quality <span>directly shapes execution</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ USE CASES ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-cases">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow clay">Use cases</span>
        <h2>Where meaning must survive movement.</h2>
        <p>Wherever a message changes hands — between people, teams, formats or agents — Orient keeps intent intact.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="ab-cases-grid reveal">
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">01</div>
          <h4>Leadership &amp; Strategy</h4>
          <p>Make strategy and priorities understood consistently across the whole organisation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">02</div>
          <h4>Internal Alignment</h4>
          <p>Turn internal communication into shared understanding across teams, functions and audiences.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">03</div>
          <h4>Customer Communication</h4>
          <p>Help customers understand, adopt and succeed faster — from first touch through implementation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">04</div>
          <h4>R&amp;D &amp; Research Synthesis</h4>
          <p>Turn fragmented research into structured, reusable understanding the whole team can build on.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">05</div>
          <h4>Regulation &amp; Governance</h4>
          <p>Make complex regulation clear, traceable and usable — with evidence carried alongside.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">06</div>
          <h4>Operations &amp; Cross-functional</h4>
          <p>Align teams around the same operating reality, so work doesn't fork into competing versions of the truth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ab-card">
          <div class="num">07</div>
          <h4>Knowledge &amp; Expertise Transfer</h4>
          <p>Capture expert reasoning before it disappears — and keep it usable long after.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ MISSION ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-mission reveal">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="pre">Our mission is to make organisational understanding observable, durable and improvable — a system where strategy, decisions and communication move with coherence, and where you can measure whether meaning actually held.</p>
      <blockquote>The next advantage won't come from producing more. It will come from being <span class="em">understood</span>.</blockquote>
      <div class="attr">The Orient Team · Building infrastructure for alignment</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ CONTACT ============ -->
  <section class="section ab-contact">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="ab-contact-grid">
        <div>
          <div class="role">Visit Orient</div>
          <h2>Stockholm.</h2>
          <address>
            Orient<br />
            Malmskillnadsgatan 32<br />
            111 51 Stockholm<br />
            Sweden
          </address>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="role">Contact</div>
          <p class="who"><b>Mikael Larsson</b></p>
          <p class="who"><a href="mailto:mikael@orientos.ai">mikael@orientos.ai</a></p>
          <p class="note">Reach out about demos, partnerships, press, or whether Orient is a fit for your organisation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ CLOSING CTA ============ -->
  <section class="closing" id="access">
    <div class="wrap">
      <img src="/logomark.svg" alt="" class="closing-mark" />
      <h2>Build durable alignment.</h2>
      <p>Orient is infrastructure for keeping understanding coherent as it moves. Request access to the platform.</p>
      <form class="waitlist onink" data-waitlist data-success="On the list ✓" style="justify-content:center">
        <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="you@company.com" aria-label="Work email" required />
        <button class="btn" type="submit">Request access</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<!-- ============ FOOTER ============ -->
<footer class="site-footer">
  <div class="wrap row">
    <a href="/" class="brand" aria-label="Orient — home">
      <img src="/logo-light.svg" alt="Orient" class="brand-logo footer-logo" />
    </a>
    <div class="line">A meaning operating system for humans and machines.</div>
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/">What is Orient</a>
      <a href="/forhumans">For Humans</a>
      <a href="/formachines">For Machines</a>
      <a href="/usecases">Use cases</a>
      <a href="#top">About</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</footer>

<script is:inline src="/landing.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
